    • Constructor Detail

      • RuleImpl

        public RuleImpl(Conjunction<PositiveLiteral> head,
                Conjunction<Literal> body)
        Creates a Rule with a non-empty body and an non-empty head. All variables in the body must be universally quantified; all variables in the head that do not occur in the body must be existentially quantified.
        Parameters:
        head - list of Literals (negated or non-negated) representing the rule body conjuncts.
        body - list of positive (non-negated) Literals representing the rule head conjuncts.
